  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And he said, unto you it is given to know the mysteries of the kingdom of God,.... The doctrines of the Gospel, which to have spiritual knowledge is a special and peculiar gift of God. The Vulgate Latin and Persic versions read, \"the mystery\", in the singular, as in Mark: \"but to others in parables\"; that is, the doctrines of the Gospel are delivered in a parabolical way to others; to such as \"are without\", as the Evangelist Mark expresses it, who are strangers and foreigners, and not children, who are not the favourites of heaven, and the disciples of Christ: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that seeing they might not see, and hearing, they might not understand; what was delivered to them; see the following notes. See Gill on Matthew 13:11, Matthew 13:12, Matthew 13:13 ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "that seeing they might not see, and hearing, they might not understand; what was delivered to them; see the following notes. See Gill on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 13:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 13:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 13:13",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
